headline.main: WINANT, PRESIDENT HOLD PHONE TALK; ' Long Conversation' Reported From Hyde Park as Envoy Works on Report Here CONFERENCE ON TUESDAY His Paper Will Be Submitted Then -- Hull Also to Receive Latest Data on Britain

lead_paragraph: John G. Winant, United States Ambassador to the Court of St. James, said yesterday at the Hotel Roosevelt, where he is staying, that he had talked by telephone with President Roosevelt at Hyde Park and would report to the President in Washington on Tuesday.
abstract: Amb Winant and Roosevelt conf by telephone; former drafts rept
